STATEMENTS BY MEMBERS 
Mr. John McKay (Scarborough East, Lib.):
As originally a member of the Scarborough swim club and presently with the University of Toronto, Liz represented Canada with pride and accomplished a great feat.  
She is now training to go to the World Cup in Edmonton on November 28 as a member of the Canadian swim team. 
Liz was telling my daughter and I that she practices six hours a day.  
I congratulate Liz. 
She is a role model for what dedication, hard work and perseverance can achieve. 
Canada is proud of her. 
I wish her luck in her next event.  
