MEDICARE 
Mr. Bill Blaikie (Winnipeg-Transcona, NDP):
Mr. Speaker, tonight the Canadian Medical Association will induct Tommy Douglas into its hall of fame. 
Tommy would be pleased to see how much things have changed since the doctors' strike in Saskatchewan, how the medical community itself appreciates the virtues of publicly funded health insurance and how they are, along with others, trying to save it from death by underfunding.  
Tommy's warning in his final years about medicare was ``Don't let them take it away.'' 
The NDP urges all Canadians to heed his warning and keep an eye on the Reformers and the Liberals.  
